<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="966" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-30T22:00:00+08:00">July 30,
                                    1949—10 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 30—11:33 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1663. Exit permits being issued today and local Communist authorities
                            have tentatively fixed Tuesday morning August 2 as date for my departure
                            Nanking (see Embtel 1645 of July 29). Consequently that will by [<hi rend="italic">be</hi>] my ETD unless I advise to the contrary. Time
                            of take-off 8 a. m.</p>
                        <p>Taipei and Canton please inform appropriate authorities CAF change my
                            ETD.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 1663, repeated EmbOff Canton 697, Shanghai 922, Taipei
                            73.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>